e either  A bank statement showing a minimum of 6000 Euros  approx   9 046 US at the current rate of exchange   1 Dec 2009  or A letter signed by your parents that they will support you for the duration of your stay in Germany  Most cadets choose the second option  in which case they should bring a notarized copy of the letter to the municipal authority and send a second copy to the nearest German consulate in the US so that they will have it on file  To find the closest German consulate to your home town  check the following  http www germany info org relaunch info missions consulates html PHPSESSID e5a2bfe54d55d4cfdf46323eceda1b0f It is best to arrange with your hosts in advance of your arrival regarding transportation to the UniBw campus  When you leave Germany to return home  please take care of the formality of leaving your forwarding address with the municipal authorities  this is called Abmeldung  Col  Sunnen Home Courses Instructional Bundeswehr Exchange Conference Papers Foreign Links VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 